<subSubSection id="C337088DF77EB13FB182FBBE31A74614" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F77EB13FB182FBBE36014671" blockId="11.[151,1437,908,2015]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F77EB13FB182FBBE32C2471A" box="[199,251,1089,1115]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: Wahlberg, in his description, gave data for both male and female. According to Sundevall’s acquisition catalogue, 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF77EB13FB0D2FB9B3008473D" box="[407,561,1124,1151]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">four syntypes</specimenCount>
of this species were received in Stockholm after Wahlberg’s death. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77EB13FB405FB9B336347E1" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." pageId="11" pageNumber="532" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 65)</bibRefCitation>
referred to two “types”, so we cannot regard them as 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F77EB13FB289FB77360A47E0" box="[972,1075,1160,1186]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">lectotype</typeStatus>
designations. The original type series consists of 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF77EB13FB024FB5333C74785" box="[353,510,1196,1223]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">four syntypes</specimenCount>
: NRM 568749 [11689], an adult male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F77EB13FB562FB5236F74785" box="[1063,1230,1196,1223]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" value="1854-08-07">7 August 1854</date>
at Swakop River; NRM 568750 [11691], an adult female collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F77EB13FB3FBFB2F316047A9" box="[702,857,1232,1259]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" value="1854-04-29">29 April 1854</date>
at 
<collectingCountry id="F33A1B96F77EB13FB23EFB2F31C547A9" box="[891,1020,1232,1259]" name="Namibia" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">Walvis Bay</collectingCountry>
(both of these referred to as types by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77EB13FB1D2FB0B33A3464D" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[151,410,1268,1295]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe 1926: 65</bibRefCitation>
); NRM 90168195 [11692], a juvenile male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F77EB13FB2B3FB0B36E8464D" box="[1014,1233,1268,1295]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" value="1854-09-18">18 September 1854</date>
at Swakop River; and NRM 90168197 [11690], an adult male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F77EB13FB3B1FAE731B64671" box="[756,911,1304,1331]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" value="1854-04-27">27 April 1854</date>
at 
<collectingCountry id="F33A1B96F77EB13FB2F4FAE7360D4671" box="[945,1076,1304,1331]" name="Namibia" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">Walvis Bay</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B925B06F77EB13FB182FAC231A74614" blockId="11.[151,1437,908,2015]" box="[199,926,1340,1367]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">
